textBox.richText: Wint was born and raised in Myanmar (formally known as Burma). She grew up in a big family and is the youngest of five children. She received her bachelor of dental surgery in 2007 in Myanmar. After practicing general dentistry for a few years, she immigrated to US in 2009. She then went to UCSF International Dentist Program and received D.D.S. She is currently a second year orthodontic resident at UCSF. In her free time, Wint enjoys traveling, joining Zumba Class, spending time with her husband, cooking Burmese food and trying different cuisines.
